01:18:07.921 --> 01:18:14.230
So a note about normalization.

01:18:14.230 --> 01:18:17.690
I kind of skipped on
this over the last one.

01:18:17.690 --> 01:18:23.400
p is a probability in this
6N dimensional phase space.

01:18:23.400 --> 01:18:32.820
So the normalization is that the
integral over all of the p i's

01:18:32.820 --> 01:18:42.470
and qi's should be equal to 1.

01:18:42.470 --> 01:18:46.640
And so this omega,
more precisely,

01:18:46.640 --> 01:18:49.920
when we are not talking
about discrete numbers,

01:18:49.920 --> 01:18:53.530
is the quantity
that I have to put

01:18:53.530 --> 01:18:58.890
so that when I integrate this
over phase space, I will get 1.

01:18:58.890 --> 01:19:03.940
So basically, if I write this
in the form that I have written,

01:19:03.940 --> 01:19:11.830
you can see that omega is
obtained by integrating over

01:19:11.830 --> 01:19:18.850
p i q i that correspond
to this accessible states.

01:19:25.290 --> 01:19:27.670
It's kind of like
a delta function.

01:19:27.670 --> 01:19:32.240
Basically, there's huge
portions of phase space

01:19:32.240 --> 01:19:38.060
that are 0 probability,
and then there's

01:19:38.060 --> 01:19:43.990
a surface that has
the probability that

01:19:43.990 --> 01:19:48.610
is 1 over omega and it is
the area of that surface

01:19:48.610 --> 01:19:52.000
that I have to ensure
is appearing here,

01:19:52.000 --> 01:19:54.730
so that when I integrate
over that area of one

01:19:54.730 --> 01:19:59.070
over that area, I will get one.

01:19:59.070 --> 01:20:03.230
Now, the part that corresponds
to the q coordinates

01:20:03.230 --> 01:20:06.190
is actually very
simple, because the q

01:20:06.190 --> 01:20:09.340
coordinates have to
be inside the box.

01:20:09.340 --> 01:20:12.820
Each one of them has a volume
v, so the coordinate part

01:20:12.820 --> 01:20:16.041
of the integral
gives me v to the m.

01:20:16.041 --> 01:20:16.540
OK?

01:20:19.330 --> 01:20:24.170
Now, the momentum
part, the momenta

01:20:24.170 --> 01:20:26.480
are constrained by
something like this.

01:20:30.640 --> 01:20:38.040
I can rewrite that as sum over
i p i squared equals to 2mE.

01:20:41.500 --> 01:20:47.290
And if I regard this 2mE as
something like r squared,

01:20:47.290 --> 01:20:49.680
like a radius
squared, you can see

01:20:49.680 --> 01:20:52.310
that this is like
the equation that you

01:20:52.310 --> 01:20:54.620
would have for
the generalization

01:20:54.620 --> 01:20:57.600
of the sphere in 3N dimensions.

01:20:57.600 --> 01:21:00.090
Because if I had
just x squared, x

01:21:00.090 --> 01:21:03.030
squared plus y squared
is r squared is a circle,

01:21:03.030 --> 01:21:05.140
x squared plus y
squared plus z squared

01:21:05.140 --> 01:21:07.700
is r squared is
a sphere, so this

01:21:07.700 --> 01:21:15.410
is the hypersphere
in 3N dimensions.

01:21:18.160 --> 01:21:22.740
So when I do the
integrations over q,

01:21:22.740 --> 01:21:32.880
I have to integrate
over the surface of a 3N

01:21:32.880 --> 01:21:45.270
dimensional hypersphere of
radius square root of 2m.

01:21:47.850 --> 01:21:49.744
OK?

01:21:49.744 --> 01:21:54.140
And there is a simple
formula for that.

01:21:54.140 --> 01:21:59.800
This surface area,
in general, is

01:21:59.800 --> 01:22:03.460
going to be
proportional to r raised

01:22:03.460 --> 01:22:07.880
to the power of
dimension minus 1.

01:22:07.880 --> 01:22:12.210
And there's the generalization
of 2pi r over 4pi r squared

01:22:12.210 --> 01:22:14.940
that you would have in
two or three dimensions,

01:22:14.940 --> 01:22:17.900
which we will discuss next time.

01:22:17.900 --> 01:22:22.170
It is 2 to the
power of 3n over 2

01:22:22.170 --> 01:22:26.980
divided by 3n over 2 factorial.

01:22:26.980 --> 01:22:29.950
So we have the formula
for this omega.

